text: Monaro Panthers Football Club, formerly called Inter Monaro Soccer Club, is an Australian semi-professional soccer club based in Queanbeyan, a city in New South Wales. It competes in the National Premier Leagues Capital Football (NPL ACT) in the Australian Capital Territory. The club was founded by Italian Australians, who gave it the name "Inter Monaro" after the Italian club Inter Milan and the Monaro region (where Queanbeyan is located). It has strong connections to Queanbeyan's Italian community. Category:Soccer clubs in New South Wales
title: Monaro Panthers FC
